Attulus floricola is a species of jumping spider (family Salticidae) with a Palearctic distribution. They are typically 4–4.5 millimetres (0.16–0.18 in) in length. Females are dark reddish brown, with an almost black anterior.Formerly, it was placed in the genus Sitticus and then from 2017 to 2020 in the genus Calositticus.